assetProfile.longBusinessSummary: IDEA Consultants,Inc. provides integrated consultancy services on social infrastructure development and environmental conservation projects in Japan and internationally. The company offers research, plans, designs, manages, evaluates, and consulting services related to construction and environmental conservation and improvement; environment work related services, such as surveys, predictions, analyses, impact assessments, and environmental conservation measures; and physical and chemical analysis, and testing of water quality, air quality, soil, waste, tap water, food, etc. It also manufactures, sales, and leases environmental research and analysis equipment; industrial and household waste recycling services; building and structure design and management services; civil engineering and construction work services; and surveying and geological surveys, as well as real estate acquisition, sales, leases, brokerage, maintenance, management, and consulting services. In addition, the company provides purchases and sales machinery, instruments, parts, and tools; and temporary staffing services, as well as manufactures, processes, and sells honey, royal jelly, pollen, etc. Further, it offers environmental consulting services, including environmental assessment/environmental planning, conservation, regeneration and creation of the natural environment, environmental survey, chemical analysis and risk assessment, life science, and sustainability management support; construction consulting services comprising land conservation, transportation/logistics infrastructure, urban and regional development, and disaster response and recovery/reconstruction; and information system, such as disaster prevention/environment/construction system development, system operation support, weather, disaster prevention, and life information service, as well as infrastructure management services. The company was founded in 1953 and is headquartered in Tokyo, Japan.
